  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-09-12",
    "date": "2022-11-03T16:31:56Z",
    "text": "This bill prohibits the District of Columbia (DC) from using federal or local funds to require that students in elementary or secondary schools receive a COVID-19 vaccination. The bill also nullifies the Coronavirus Immunization of School Students and Early Childhood Workers Regulation Amendment Act of 2021 (D.C. Act 24-85), enacted by the DC Council on January 12, 2022."
